\caption{
Imaginary part of the RN QNM frequencies as a function of charge for
$n=10,~30,~60,~5000$. For $n=5000$ we also display the actually
computed points, and compare to the prediction of the analytic formula
(\ref{MNf}). As for the real part, the oscillations are reproduced
extremely well, but the disagreement with our numerical data increases
for small charge.
}
